name: Bottersnikes & Gumbles
overview: In a far away forgotten valley heaped with long-abandoned junk, a timeless battle rages between good and evil… and also between squishy and scaly, happy and grumpy, clever and wily… handsome and plain old ugly. This is the land of Bottersnikes and Gumbles.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: The fun-loving Gumbles bounce and play while staying away from the foul-smelling Bottersnikes who live in a nearby junkyard.

episodes.name: The Gumbledex
episodes.overview: Tink is desperate to get his name into the Gumbledex, a record of outstanding Gumble achievements, and so sets out to break a record.

episodes.name: King Sized Calamity
episodes.overview: Happi has finally finished building his Gumbly Horn and wants to put on a performance, but then Bounce breaks the spring that powers the horn.

episodes.name: Song of the Bottersnikes
episodes.overview: Merri and Jolli leave the Gumbletree after overhearing Tink insulting their singing, but when WeatherSnike hears them, she is dazzled.

episodes.name: The Spangler
episodes.overview: When the ball from their game of pock-pock ends up in the hands of the Bottersnikes, Tink, Bounce and Willi try to retrieve it.

episodes.name: Undercover Gumble
episodes.overview: Tink finds a Bottersnike disguise in the junkyard and puts it on to scare his friends, but then he is mistaken for a real Snike by Snorg and Glob.

episodes.name: Up, Up and Away
episodes.overview: Bounce is determined to conquer all the highest summits in the junkyard, but when she tries to scale one in Snike Hill she climbs so high that she freezes, loses her stretch and risks capture by the Snikes.

episodes.name: Grubloom Day
episodes.overview: Grubloom Day is the one day of the year when a rare flower blooms and delivers up delicious grubs for the Gumbles, but when Bounce eats Willi's share, she is determined to make it right, and sets off to Snike Hill to find another Grubloom.

episodes.name: Gumble Rally
episodes.overview: All the Gumbles are competing in the Gumble Rally, a fast-paced race through the junkyard, but they run into the Bottersnikes who have set up camp in the middle of the course, leaving Merri and Jolli to overcome their bickering to work together and rescue their friends.

episodes.name: Toot on Duty
episodes.overview: When a nasty case of the Snike flu spreads through the Gumbletree, Toot is forced to overcome his greatest fear and venture back to Snike Hill to retrieve the only known cure for the flu - mattress stuffing.

episodes.name: Gumble Magnetism
episodes.overview: Tink steals the Bottersnike's giant magnet, but instead of destroying it as planned, Tink, Bounce and Willi decide to use it to barricade the Snikes into Snike Hill.

episodes.name: The King's Seat
episodes.overview: Tink mistakes the sun reflecting off a discarded toilet seat as a special weapon.

episodes.name: Burples
episodes.overview: Willi stumbles upon a baby Snike conjured up from one of Smiggles dreams.

episodes.name: Abominable Gumble
episodes.overview: Tink tries to trick the Snikes into thinking there is a Snike-eating Gumble on the loose.

episodes.name: This Means Peace
episodes.overview: Tink must work with his nemesis Glob in order to return to safety.

episodes.name: King Prisoner
episodes.overview: When the Snike King launches an attack on the Gumbletree, Tink manages to shrink him in the water and take him as their prisoner.

episodes.name: The Monster in the Moat
episodes.overview: After twice mistakenly claiming to have seen a monster, Willi is reluctant to be made a fool of again and doesn't alert anyone when he spots something suspicious under the Gumbletree. But when the Snikes kidnap his friends, it's up to Willi to save them.

episodes.name: The Blame Game
episodes.overview: When Tink, Bounce and Willi find themselves trapped on Snike Hill with no memory of their capture, they try to recall what happened, but Tink and Bounce have very different versions of events, each placing the other at fault.

episodes.name: Gumble Grabba
episodes.overview: When the Bottersnikes discover they need smaller hands to reach some sofa rot in their mattress mine, they use Gubbo's new Gumble-grabber to snatch the Gumbles from the Gumbletree to do it for them, leaving Float to mount a solo rescue.

episodes.name: Sammi Whammi Gumble
episodes.overview: After learning of Happi's failed experiment to send a Gumble into space, Tink becomes determined to try it, but when he is detached from his safety rope, Happi must launch himself into space to save Tink.

episodes.name: Those Magnificent Gumbles
episodes.overview: Float is growing increasingly annoyed by Merri and Jolli distracting her search for the mythical three-headed dump dragon, but when she tells them to go and play in the storm, and they end up captured in Snike Hill, Float feels responsible and mounts an ingenious rescue mission.

episodes.name: Captain Grate-Face
episodes.overview: After getting a grater stuck on his head, Willi is mistaken by the other gumbles for the legendary, snike-slaying Captain Grate Face, and finally starts getting the respect he deserves, but when the snikes show up, Willi must either come clean or live up to his newly acquired heroic reputation.

episodes.name: Tink's Big Stink
episodes.overview: After Tink recklessly stinks out the Gumbletree, he tries to behave more responsibly as he leads the gumbles on a snike lookout, but when he takes his responsible attitude too far, he gets Merri and Jolli captured by snikes and must revert to his old, impulsive habits to save the day.

episodes.name: The Sneaky Snike
episodes.overview: Happi is teaching gumblecraft to try to instill its virtues into the other gumbles, but when the snikes destroy the dodge gumble pitch during the class, the gumbles blame Happi, who sets out to prove the worth of gumblecraft by using it to trap the snikes.

episodes.name: Blue Grub Moon
episodes.overview: When a blue moon causes blue grubs to spring from the ground, Happi warns the other gumbles about the dangers of eating them, but Merri accidentally eats one, and turns into a fierce weregumble, charging into Snike Hill looking for prey.

episodes.name: Gumble Pie
episodes.overview: When Tink is assigned lookout duty while the other gumbles pick berries, he builds a dummy to cover for him, but when his failure to keep a lookout allows the snikes to approach, they mistake the dummy for a real gumble and take it to the King, leading the other gumbles to launch a rescue mission for what they think is Tink!

episodes.name: Cloudy with a Chance of Gumbles
The Return of Sammi Whammi Gumble

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: The fun-loving Gumbles bounce and play while staying away from the foul-smelling Bottersnikes who live in a nearby junkyard.
